definition.value: A uronate obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any penturonic acid.
A penturonate obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any arabinuronic acid.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 35 carbons in total with 3 double bonds.

A secondary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-isopropoxybenzoic acid with the primary amino group of 2-methylquinolin-8-amine. An allosteric activator of sarco/endoplasmic reticulum Ca(2+)-ATPase (SERCA).
Any compound that activates Sarcoplasmic/Endoplasmic Reticulum Calcium-ATPase (EC 7.2.2.10).
